  <bch:expr> <bch:tm> <bch:tm>     <dbl> <bch:byt>    <dbl>
1 f6(n)         209ms    215ms      4.57    1.15MB     16.7
2 f7(n)         195ms    196ms      5.07    1.22MB     15.2
```


:::
:::




#### Example 3

We can assign `1:n` to `z` instead of initializing it as an empty vector, thus rendering the assignment of `i` to `z[i]` in the last else statement unnecessary:




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
f8 <- function(n) {
  z <- 1:n
  for(i in z) {
    div3 <- (i %% 3 == 0)
    div5 <- (i %% 5 == 0)
    if(div3 && div5) {
      z[i] <- "FizzBuzz"
    } else if(div3) {
      z[i] <- "Fizz"
    } else if(div5) {
      z[i] <- "Buzz"
    } 
  }
  z
}
```
:::




